               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Laṭāʾif-i qudsī by Rukn al-Dīn Miskīn</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1099-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Chishtī Ṣūfī hagiography of the eminent Indian saint, 
                <persName key="person_f8102" role="subject">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Quddūs Ḥanafī al-Chishtī</persName>(d. 944/1537) of 
                <placeName>Gangoh</placeName>(
                <placeName>Saharanpur</placeName>), written by 
                <persName key="person_f8025" role="aut">[Shaykh] Rukn al-Dīn Miskīn</persName>(d. 983/1575), apparently the son of the saint, who persistently refers in Arabic to the saint as 
                <q>shaykhī va vālidī</q>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work additionally contains a wealth of information and observations on social life and politics during the transition between the last of the 
                <orgName>Lodi dynasty</orgName>and the Timurid 
                <persName key="viaf_97090468" role="oth">Emperor Bābur</persName>(d. 936/1530).
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at end.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. Datable to the early eighteenth century.</p>
                        <p>Note (f. 55A) inserted between ff. 55-56, with Arabic phrases from ritual prayers, and on the verso ingredients for food.</p>
                        <p>Nastaʿlīq tending to shikastah written tightly, with awkward naskh for Arabic passages.</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins in a neat nastaʿlīq hand within ruled frames.</p>
                        <p>Catchwords cropped.</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. Persian foliation on the verso of folios.</p>
                        <p>IOL red half-leather binding; lacking date stamp.</p>
                        <p>Folios remounted and rebound, margins torn or cropped; wormholes; gauze overlay throughout.</p>
                        <p>Ownership marks and seal at beginning.</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22922">Laṭāʾif-i qudsī</title>
